115
00:06:55,790 --> 00:06:58,334
<i>I’m protecting you because I want to, Joe.</i>

116
00:07:00,044 --> 00:07:01,421
You didn't break me.

117
00:07:03,172 --> 00:07:05,466
You opened your heart to me.

118
00:07:09,554 --> 00:07:11,180
We're soulmates, Joe.

119
00:07:13,766 --> 00:07:17,186
[Joe]<i> What the fuck?</i>

120
00:07:17,478 --> 00:07:19,480
[opening music playing]

121
00:07:25,903 --> 00:07:26,903
Joe?

122
00:07:28,906 --> 00:07:30,700
Please, say something.

123
00:07:36,789 --> 00:07:38,124
What about Ellie?

124
00:07:39,834 --> 00:07:40,834
[knocking on door]

125
00:07:42,503 --> 00:07:45,047
Ellie? We have to talk about your sister.

126
00:07:50,928 --> 00:07:51,928
Hey.

127
00:07:52,346 --> 00:07:55,933
- It's okay, all right? I come in peace.
- At, like, three in the morning.

128
00:07:56,017 --> 00:07:57,017
I mean, come on.

129
00:07:58,436 --> 00:08:00,855
Do you know
Delilah's been getting death threats?

130
00:08:02,106 --> 00:08:03,106
Yeah, I do.

131
00:08:03,608 --> 00:08:06,608
And I was actually thinkingthat you might
be able to help me out with that.

132
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:08,320
How?

133
00:08:09,405 --> 00:08:10,405
Uh... [sighs]

134
00:08:11,949 --> 00:08:16,287
I don't know, just walk me through
some of the stuff around Henderson.

135
00:08:16,746 --> 00:08:19,081
Anything you might remember
that stands out.

136
00:08:19,665 --> 00:08:21,167
No detail too small.

137
00:08:22,251 --> 00:08:24,253
That sound chill?

138
00:08:25,004 --> 00:08:27,715
I know this routine
from every movie I've ever seen.

139
00:08:28,758 --> 00:08:30,384
You're trying to entrap me.

140
00:08:30,468 --> 00:08:31,844
[Love]<i> Ellie's gonna be fine.</i>

141
00:08:32,345 --> 00:08:34,430
And you don't think I would... You know...

142
00:08:35,515 --> 00:08:37,517
If I didn't have a plan for her.

143
00:08:38,809 --> 00:08:40,061
Oh, you have a plan?

144
00:08:40,561 --> 00:08:42,104
It's simple.

145
00:08:43,397 --> 00:08:46,901
First, we make Ellie a suspect
in Henderson's murder.

146
00:08:46,984 --> 00:08:49,028
- What?
- Don't judge yet, okay?

147
00:08:49,111 --> 00:08:50,196
Let me finish.

148
00:08:50,821 --> 00:08:51,989
Step one,

149
00:08:52,073 --> 00:08:56,953
we frame Ellie for Henderson's murder
with an anonymous tip.

150
00:08:57,036 --> 00:08:59,622
